rtifact with concrete diagnostic information, verify that implement reads this `grounding`, and verify the final `plan` artifact reflects or incorporates that grounding information.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":"Integration is the minimum because grounding persistence across skill boundaries is a cross-module property. Unit tests of individual skills would verify they read/write to correct keys, but would not catch the failure where grounding is lost in the transition between skills. Only running the full pipeline with shared artifact storage can verify end-to-end flow.","level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.05,"Integration":0.85,"System":0.05,"Agentic":0.02,"Workflow":0.03}},{"behavior_id":5,"description":"When grounding is absent, implement falls back safely and emits valid plan artifact without corrupting other stored artifacts","minimum_level":"Unit","justification":"This is error-handling and fallback logic within the implement skill. A unit test mocking artifact read to return None can verify that the fallback is correctly implemented. The mock isolates the error path without requiring real infrastructure or cross-module interaction.","test_description":"Unit test mocking the artifact read operation to return None (simulating absent grounding). Call implement stage with typical inputs. Assert: (a) no exception is raised, (b) write(key='plan', ...) is called with a valid fallback plan, (c) write method is not called with corrupt or invalid data, (d) no unexpected writes to other artifacts occur as a side effect of the missing grounding.","plan_consistent":true,"plan_consistent_note":null,"level_probabilities":{"Unit":0.82,"Integration":0.15,"System":0.02,"Agentic":0,"Workflow":0.01}}]},"caller":{"type":"direct"}}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":10,"cache_creation_input_tokens":13271,"cache_read_input_tokens":0,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":13271},"output_tokens":1,"servic